                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13114372" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Sun, 25 Sep 2011 21:31:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch simply decrefs newSearchHolder if the executor rejects the task&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13114374" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Sun, 25 Sep 2011 21:32:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;whoops - patch is slightly stale - what I will actually commit also propagates the exception - right after decref, throw e.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13114442" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Mon, 26 Sep 2011 02:57:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As I&apos;m stressing tests to track down other failures, I&apos;ve learned of another subtlety in this - in some cases you need to decrement twice on error.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13114443" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Mon, 26 Sep 2011 03:09:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;And of course this should be done for the other submits...just hit this same issue on a different submit call in the autocommit test...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13148878" author="simonw" created="Sat, 12 Nov 2011 00:10:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;mark, I see several commits for this issue - can we resolve this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13149137" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Sat, 12 Nov 2011 20:21:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Open because I have not done it on 3.x yet, just trunk - I can try and do it tomorrow night, but it&apos;s certainly not critical (more a problem for tests than anything else), so could also go to 3.6 easily.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13189374" author="lancenorskog" created="Thu, 19 Jan 2012 20:52:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is it possible that this bug was in Solr 1.4.1?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13264916" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Mon, 30 Apr 2012 13:09:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;not going to 3x at this point&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
